# bwrap placeholder directory

This directory holds a static bwrap binary (`bwrap`) that is bundled with
the Linux sandbox helper in CI/release builds.

The Rust helper (`helper-linux/src/main.rs`) discovers it automatically via
`bwrap_binary()` — it checks for `bwrap/bwrap` relative to the helper
executable's directory.

## Development

This `.gitkeep` file keeps the directory in version control so the CI
packaging step can place the binary here. Do not remove.

For local testing without a bundled binary:
- Ensure `bwrap` is available on `PATH`, or
- Set `SYNERGY_BWRAP=/path/to/bwrap` as an environment variable
